  "text": "When torque angles were 0, our results were in accordance with the findings of Kusy and Whitley [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ( Table I ). The archwire width had no effect on the critical contact angles when the torque angles were 0. However, as the torque angle increased, the archwire width had an effect on the critical contact angle as a function of torque angle. In addition, as the torque angle increased, the critical contact angles decreased for all archwire-bracket combinations. These results show that the critical contact angle decreases in a nonlinear manner with increased torque angulation.",
